Name: Mirch Masala
Address: Opposite Embassy Center Beside R K Cycle Store Mota Bazaar Vallabh Vidyanagar
Review: Mirch masala is really famous for its non veg dishes. This restaurant’s theme is purely based on Bollywood. Value for money is bit high but the taste of food is fabulous. The place where I live I.e Anand they have a chaat corner attached with the restaurant itself. Today we had chole tikki and jalebi. The chole tikki was okay okay not that good as I expected but the jalebi oh my god was so big in size and they serve 3 pieces of that big jalebi at 90 bucks which is totally an worth to eat 🤭. The jalebis were pretty crispy and purely made with ghee. They also have different types of chaat dahi Bhalla, dahi papdi chaat, aloo tikki, gajar ka halwa and many more
